Makes the hardcoded "Store" lastname of the store-pickup shipping address translatable.

Root cause: selectForShipping() hardcodes the string literal 'Store' as the shipping
address lastname. This value is later concatenated into the shipping method title
(shipping-information-ext.js) and shown to the customer, so it stays in English
regardless of the store locale.
Fix: wrap it in $t('Store'), using the mage/translate dependency already imported
into this module as $t.

diff --git a/view/frontend/web/js/model/pickup-locations-service.js b/view/frontend/web/js/model/pickup-locations-service.js
index 57a3df1..db30022 100644
--- a/view/frontend/web/js/model/pickup-locations-service.js
+++ b/view/frontend/web/js/model/pickup-locations-service.js
@@ -115,7 +115,7 @@ define([
                 {},
                 addressConverter.formAddressDataToQuoteAddress({
                     firstname: location.name,
-                    lastname: 'Store',
+                    lastname: $t('Store'),
                     street: location.street,
                     city: location.city,
                     postcode: location.postcode,
